description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a band 5 Registered Health Professional (Nurse, Social Worker, Occupational Therapist) to join the Harrogate Integrated Community Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will help develop your skills in a community setting, based in the beautiful spa town of Harrogate. The team covers a rural area and therefore it is essential that applicants are able to travel independently across the locality and have access to a suitable vehicle for business purposes. If necessary, adjustments can be considered in accordance with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is welcoming and thrives on supporting each other, being personable, whilst still maintaining their professionalism. We enjoy two away days each year to reflect and problem solve as a team, as well as having regular team building activities. Wellbeing is very important to us and we welcome applications from people who want to make a difference and involve service users in their care and recovery. You will be working with a caseload of service users, carrying out assessments and working in collaboration to support them in their recovery. This involves providing treatment utilising evidence-based psychological interventions for people with severe and enduring mental health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunities for preceptorship for newly qualified staff applying for the post. Internal and external training opportunities are available. An interest in physical health monitoring is preferential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Donald Wilson, Team Manager, Harrogate Integrated Community Team, Windsor House, Harrogate, HG1 2PW. Tel: 01423 852000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rob O&#39;Hagan, Advanced Nurse Practitioner, Harrogate Integrated Community &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Team, Windsor House, Harrogate, HG1 2PW. Tel: 01423 852000.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
